docs.abstract: Contractors crucial to clearing vegetation around power lines face higher coverage costs because of potential liability in later disasters.
docs.snippet: Contractors crucial to clearing vegetation around power lines face higher coverage costs because of potential liability in later disasters.
docs.lead_paragraph: PARADISE, Calif. — D.J. Gomes and his logging crew were working in California’s wine country last fall, helping clear vegetation away from power lines and reduce the ever-growing wildfire risk. While they were gone, fire came for their hometown.

headline.main: California’s Latest Wildfire Problem: Insuring the Tree Trimmers
headline.print_headline: When Fire Insurance Is the Hindrance

docs.abstract: The limited deal will give American farmers more access to Japan and serve as a bright spot for the president on an otherwise troubled trade front.

docs.abstract: The renminbi fell past the key point of 7 to the U.S. dollar, in a signal that Beijing may be willing to use devaluation as a trade war weapon.
docs.snippet: The renminbi fell past the key point of 7 to the U.S. dollar, in a signal that Beijing may be willing to use devaluation as a trade war weapon.
docs.lead_paragraph: BEIJING — China’s currency weakened past the psychologically important point of 7 to the American dollar for the first time in more than a decade, a move that reflects the growing severity of the trade war with the United States and that could indicate Beijing’s growing desire to find ways to retaliate against President Trump.

headline.main: China’s Currency Weakens in a Potential Challenge to Trump
headline.print_headline: China’s Currency Weakens in a Potential Challenge to Trump
